               <t:note>
                  <t:ab type="history">ʾAzazo is a town located 13 km ca.
                     southwest of the historic city of <t:placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LOC3577Gondar">Gondar</t:placeName>. During the <t:date>17th century</t:date>, it became a major
                     religious and political centre and it remained a royal residence and a
                     residence of the <t:roleName type="function">ʾǝč̣č̣age</t:roleName> for much of the
                        <t:date>18th and 19th century</t:date>. Under <t:roleName type="title">ʾaṣe</t:roleName>
                     <t:persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS9038Susenyos">Susǝnyos</t:persName> it became an important
                     residence for both the <t:roleName type="function">Emperor</t:roleName> and the
                     Jesuits. It remained the seat of the <t:roleName type="function">ʾǝč̣č̣age</t:roleName> until the 
                     <t:date>19th century</t:date>, even after the
                     establishment of the quarter of <t:placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LOC6535EccBet">ʾƎč̣č̣age
                        Bet</t:placeName> in <t:placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LOC3577Gondar">Gondar</t:placeName>. ʾAzazo
                     was the place where the monastery of <t:placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LOC2297DabraL">Dabra
                        Libānos</t:placeName> was relocated from the <t:placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LOC5597Sawa">Šawā</t:placeName> (cfr. <t:placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LOC1670AzazoT">ʾAzazo Takla
                        Hāymānot</t:placeName>). </t:ab>
               </t:note>
